Cognitive Fallacy - Number 1

The Fallacy - Hypothesis Myopia

  • Hypothesis Myopia is where researchers fixate on one hypothesis, and seek to gather evidence for that particular hypothesis, rather than exploring other hypotheses/ignoring other possibilities, questioning their hypothesis validity, or gathering evidence that would go against their hypothesis.
